We provide the first photographic documentation of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="3CB12A1F832AFFA8FBA7FA9AFB21FA0E" box="[1113,1249,1384,1411]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–73" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[196,1407,186,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-28@24.[161,1427,181,1900]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 69–73. Male genitalia of Manitischeria sparmanniae (Puplesis &amp; Diškus) (first photographic documentation); 69, paratype, slide no. AD0433 (ZIN), ventral view, focused on uncus, tegumen and phallus; 70, same, focused on juxta and vinculum; 71, paratype, slide no. AD1023 (ZIN), lateral view; 72, same, phallus; 73, paratype, slide no. AD0433 (ZIN), juxta" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4709339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4709339/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">Figs. 69–73</figureCitation>
). Two 
<typeStatus id="7B318838832AFFA8FAD4FA9BFA58FA0E" box="[1322,1432,1385,1411]" pageId="8" pageNumber="259">paratypes</typeStatus>
, previously deposited at LEU (=VPU), will be transferred to ZIN (see Material and Methods).
